<guildfile>
  <guildbasic name="Black Tower" guildfile="Ashaman" gossip_name="btgossip" type="1" id="8" gltitle="&amp;KAsha&apos;man GL&amp;n" guildietitles="" gflags="22" guildwalk_room="13100" gold="392259">
    <desc>Asha&apos;man, the name given to followers of the Dragon Reborn, men who have come
to what is now being called the Black Tower in order to learn how to channel.
Some have dreamed of channeling despite all the dire risks, while others remain
only because passing the test for the ability to learn has itself started them
on the road to channeling, and they now must learn to control it before it
kills them.  They train not only in using the One Power, but also in the use of
the sword and in fighting with hands and feet.  Unlike Aes Sedai, who go to
great lengths to make sure that those they train are not allowed to move
dangerously fast, the Asha&apos;man are pushed hard from the beginning, most
especially in learning to use the Power&apos;s violent aspect.  It is expected that
a certain number of Asha&apos;man will die or be burned out attempting to learn.  
Bred to be honed weapons of destruction, the Asha&apos;man are surely a force to be
reckoned with.    

Once your Background has been approved there are two ways to enter the 
Black Tower. there are two types of recruitment strategies employed by
the M&apos;Hael and the Black Tower: The Lord Dragon&apos;s Amnesty and Active
Recruiting. The reasons for both seeking the amnesty and joining up with 
an active recruitment session are very similar. Among them include but
are not limited to: Pride, fame, poverty, curiosity, hope, desperation, 
and bravery.;

&amp;bAmnesty &amp;n-  The Lord Dragon issued a general amnesty to all male 
channelers in Caemlyn, the capital of Andor, a city supervised by Rand 
al&apos;Thor.  This amnesty, or pardon, purged all crimes a male channeler
might have committed, and offers sanctuary to those whom would normally 
be fatally scrutinized by society. The only fact about the amnesty that 
is clear is that it reigns over Caemlyn. All else is shrouded in mystery.

&amp;bActive Recruiting&amp;n - Active Recruiting is a strategy invented and 
implemented by Mazrim Taim. It involves parties of Asha&apos;man approaching
villages of all shapes and sizes, all over the world, to recruit young 
men of a suitable age to fight for the Lord Dragon.  What this commitment
truly entails is, however, unknown to the individual involved.
</desc>
    <reqs>\c00The first step in molding a character into an Asha&apos;man seeker is to first
determine what type of channeler you are.  Statistically the teachable 
channeler makes up just about ninety-nine percent of the male channeling
populace and due to the fact that the RP is more complex for a Spark, it
is suggested that anyone who is a beginner to RP as well as channeling,
play a teachable.

&amp;bTeachable Channelers&amp;n - These men have the innate ability to be taught how
to grasp, and then how to channel. Without assistance, they will never 
come to know or use the powers bestowed upon them by the Creator.

&amp;bSpark Channelers&amp;n - There are a very few who are born with the ability to
touch the True Source whether they wish it or not, though even they
require teaching to use their gift fully. These men are known as being
born with the spark. While typically stronger in potential strength than
others, their ability without training is minimal. Channeling without
training is extremely dangerous to your health and causes many side
effects. Under no circumstances may you role-play a seeker born with
the spark or having been sparked, without the guildleader&apos;s permission. 
Requirements include an extensive knowledge of channeling mechanics as
well as adequate role-play ability.

The next step is creating an appropriate background story. A background 
is the story about the character&apos;s past and present. It can also include 
as much relevant information about your character as possible. Please be
sure to include the answer to the following questions.  They serve only
to guide, not to limit.
&amp;b1)&amp;n How old are you?                           
&amp;b2)&amp;n Where are you from?      
&amp;b3)&amp;n What about your family and childhood? 
&amp;b4)&amp;n Do/did you have a job?                    
&amp;b5)&amp;n What are your feelings about other groups and why? 
&amp;b6)&amp;n What do you believe in?
&amp;b7)&amp;n What are your goals in life?
&amp;b8)&amp;n What are your views on Rand al&apos;Thor?

The next step is to create a list of weaknesses and strengths your 
character possesses. This is in regards any quality or attribute of your
character that defines him. For every strength you give your character, 
apply a weakness of the same intensity. Your character&apos;s background story
might very well prove to be the inspiration of many of these
characteristics. The end result should be a more realistic, complex, and
balanced character than from what you started with. As many merits and
flaws for your character as your imagination permits are welcome. 

You&apos;re done! Compile what you have, which should include:
&amp;b1)&amp;n Character&apos;s Full Name 
&amp;b2)&amp;n Character&apos;s Channeler Type 
&amp;b3)&amp;n Character&apos;s Background Story     
&amp;b4)&amp;n Character&apos;s List of Strengths and Flaws      
&amp;b5)&amp;n Character&apos;s Recruitment Preference

And send it to the Black Tower GL, or fill out the online application at:
http://www.drathus.org/blacktower
</reqs>
    <gossip>A scouting expedition was sent to Fal Moran. The city was discovered
abandoned and in ruins. There were many traps and pitfalls left in the
abandoned city, resulting in the deaths of several members of the
expedition.

--
</gossip>
